{
  "text": "Although the parameter space for RPV spectra with sparticles below a TeV has recently been reduced, the sensitivity of these bounds is driven primarily by lepton number violating processes. For purely baryonic RPV, the bounds are considerably weaker and can accommodate natural stops with \u21e0 100 GeV masses, provided they decay predominantly to dijets via\u016aDD [CITATION_1] . For RPV gluinos decaying exclusively to e g ! t e t, the strongest experimental bound is now \u21e0 > 670 GeV [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] , however, recasting R-parity conserving SUSY searches may place a stronger \u21e0 800 GeV bound on the gluino mass [CITATION_6] .",
